extends layout

block content
  h1 First question!
  h2 How many COVID-19 vaccines exist, as of June 2021

  form(action = "/submitAnswer", method = "POST")
    div
      if (!submitted)
        input(type='radio' id= 'a' name = 'answer' value = "wrong")
      label(for = 'a') Four. Pfizer-BionTech, AstraZeneca, Moderna, Johnson and Johnson.
    br
    div
      if (!submitted)
        input(type='radio' id= 'b' name = 'answer' value = "wrong")
      label(for = 'a') Only one: Pfizer-BionTech.
    br
    div
      if (!submitted)
        input(type='radio' id= 'c' name = 'answer' value = "correct")
      label(for = 'c') Internationally, there are over 15 vaccines that have been authorized for use in certain countries.
    br
    input(type='hidden' name='pagenum' value='1')
    button.btn.btn-primary(type = "submit") Submit!

  if (submitted)
    if (correct)
      p Correct!
    else
      p.incorrect Incorrect! see answer:
    p.answer As of June 2021, at there are 16 authorized vaccines, internationally (1). In Canada there are seven vaccines which are intended to be rolled out (2).
    p.answer More than 200 additional vaccine candidates are in development, of which more than 80+ are in clinical development.
    a(href="https://www.cp24.com/news/a-brief-look-at-the-seven-vaccines-canada-has-pre-ordered-1.5293435?cache=") 1. Vaccine Tracker.
    br
    a(href="https://www.raps.org/news-and-articles/news-articles/2020/3/covid-19-vaccine-tracker") 2. Vaccines in Canada.
    br

    a(href = "/2")
      button.btn.btn-info Next Question!

